# Summary

Please include a summary of the change and which issue is fixed. Please also include relevant motivation and context. List any dependencies that are required for this change.

I have added a couple of models not defined in vertex ai model provider, that were already defined in google model provider.

Let me know if you guys want me to add a _position.yaml file as well.

The added models are:

gemini-2.0-flash-thinking-exp-01-21
gemini-2.0-flash-thinking-exp-1219
gemini-exp-1114
gemini-exp-1121
gemini-exp-1206

fixes #13072

### 1. Is this request related to a challenge you're experiencing? Tell me about your story.

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8b64bc42-85fd-4fc6-b25d-8bd20d77917c)

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c0634807-028a-45e4-bee1-25b918c1eec6)

The list of Vertex AI models in Dify doesn't match the models in the Vertex AI panel; missing models need to be added. Thanks

### 2. Additional context or comments

I'd like to ask, if I enable Function calls when calling Vertex AI, will it cause the error "[vertex_ai] Error: module 'vertexai.generative_models' has no attribute 'Schema'", is this my fault, a project defect, or does Vertex AI simply not support function calls?  I would be very grateful if you could answer my question!

### 3. Can you help us with this feature?

- [ ] I am interested in contributing to this feature.
